          "title": "The agricultural-doxological cascade (vv. 9-11)",
          "body": "Paul cites Psalm 112:9 (LXX): *He scattered abroad, he gave to the poor, His righteousness endures forever.* The Psalm describes the *blessed man who fears the LORD* — his righteousness is visible in his generosity, and that righteousness endures eternally. Paul applies this to the Corinthians: God who supplies *seed to the sower and bread for food* (alluding to Isaiah 55:10) will supply and multiply *your seed for sowing* and increase *the harvest of your righteousness* (v. 10). The believer’s generosity is funded by divine supply; the resources used for giving were never self-generated. Verse 11 names the goal: *you will be enriched in everything for all liberality, which through us is producing thanksgiving to God.* Enrichment is *for* liberality, not for accumulation. The whole cycle terminates not in the giver’s satisfaction but in God’s glory."
